The paper is about natural language generation (NLG) using deep learning, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of neural models for NLG, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of large training data and generalizing properties of neural models, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the domain of video games, which could fall under the category of computer graphics (cs.CC). Finally, the paper mentions the use of crowdsourcing for data collection, which could fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
